<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Juventus are reportedly in contact with Federico Chiesa’s agent to negotiate a deal for the Fiorentina forward.  </p>

<p>The Bianconeri are said to be preparing a £45million offer that could see the Italy international relocate to Turin for the next five years.</p>

<p>However, the two parties are yet to agree terms as Fiorentina are allegedly holding out for their £64m asking price.  </p>

<p> Juventus are reportedly in contact with Federico Chiesa’s agent Fali Ramadani over deal</p>

<p>The Old Lady have added an obligation to buy next summer in a bid to convince the Viola to accept the loan deal, according to Correire.</p>

<p>Having delivered seven goals for Fiorentina last season, Andrea Pirlo is the keen to secure the 22-year-old's signature amid growing interest from AC Milan.  </p>

<p>Andrea Pirlo is the keen to secure the 22-year-old's signature amid growing interest from Milan</p>

<p> Chiesa has already scored one goal and registered one assist for Fiorentina this season</p>

<p>Chiesa - the son of former Italy striker Enrico - is rated as one of Italy's best young prospects and will be an integral part of their squad for next summer's European Championship. </p>

<p>Since breaking into the first team in 2016, Chiesa has been a hit for La Viola and has already scored one goal and registered one assist during the clubs first two games of the 2020-2021 season. </p>

<p>Fiorentina are unlikely to let their star player depart from the Artemio Franchi for a discounted price given he is under contract until June 2022.     </p>

<p>Chiesa - the son of former Italy striker Enrico (above) - is rated as one of Italy's best prospects</p>
